getAllTaxes() - Method in interface com.teksystems.salestaxexercise.tax.TaxJurisdiction
The list of taxes for a given jurisdiction must not contain any duplicate taxes and must be maintained in a particular order, as some taxes may be applied on top of other taxes prior to them on the list e.g., Quebec sales taxes are applied on top of the federal sales tax The SOLID design principle that interfaces should wherever possible depend on other interfaces, not concrete classes, would suggest this should return a Set or a List, not a LinkedHashSet.
